posts.raw_content:
Just renewed my CDL Medical Card here is what that entails:

As I have Monocular Vision an eye exam was needed. 400 dollars and an office visit that required a bunch of forms filled out.  Then an hour or so of exams and answering questions (in English).

Then I had to coax the Doctor and Staff through filling out a "VISION EVALUATION REPORT"
Form MCSA-5871

If they messed this form up then I would be screwed at the Certified CDL Med Exam and have to start over.

That was not the case (this time went through this last June everything went wrong and I am going through the process again) .

So I went to a MED RX walkin clinic for the CDL Med Exam (I recommend them for this).

I bypassed the digital login and just waited at the reception desk until she decided to do some receiving.  I had Form MCSA-5875 filled out already (Always Print This Shit Out On Some Nice Heavy Card stock. Anyone Encountering It Is Impressed) and did not have to run through filling out this form which will raise your blood pressure just filling it out.

So the exam started with a urine sample (not a drug test) looking for Protein/Blood/Diabetes then progressed to around thirty minutes of conversation (in English) that looked for: color blindness, Whispered hearing on left and right ears, height , weight, gait and several vision tests.

That went well and the late thirty young lady hopefully benefited from my words of encouragement (she thought she was a " Hot Mess").

Moving on the Doctor part of the Exam:

The Female Doctor entered the exam room wearing a mask.....

Normally that would end any encounter  but I sucked it up.

We spent about an hour going over the Form MCSA-5875  (she really like the form on the heavy cardstock) and doing some minor physical exercises. 

Then she wanted me to drop trow to check for a hernia.
Did not do a finger wave just felt either side of my gear and said that there is signs of a hernia on my right side. 

I pushed back and offered her a further exam but she walked it back.

She completely missed my umbilical hernia.

I then had to wait another 45 minutes to have the Doctor complete the form and give it to the Receptionist to submit it to FMSCA.  Then I had no assurance that they had not fucked up my CDL Med Card and if pulled over I would be ensnared in lawyers and fines.

So How The Fuck Does Someone Who Cannot Speak English Get Past This Checkpoint?????


https://www.fmcsa.dot.gov/sites/fmcsa.dot.gov/files/2022-03/Vision%20Evaluation%20Report%20Form%20MCSA-5871.pdf

https://www.fmcsa.dot.gov/sites/fmcsa.dot.gov/files/2025-04/Medical%20Examination%20Report%20Form%20MCSA-5875%20508pdf.pdf

https://www.ecfr.gov/current/title-49/subtitle-B/chapter-III/subchapter-B/part-391/subpart-E/section-391.41
